{
  "texts": [
    "Since a message always has a tree structure, we can also define evaluation tasks at the leaf level, where a leaf corresponds to an unstructured, literal field: Evaluation Metric 2.",
    "For a given message type, how many leaf fields of messages of this message type are accurately extracted or erroneously added, removed, or altered?",
    "We note that Evaluation Metric 1 is defined at a lower granularity and is more stringent than Evaluation Metric 2.",
